**Chapter 2: Game Families**

An understanding of 'Game Families' is integral to unlocking the intricacies of game assets. As several game studios follow an ecological approach of reusing and recycling game technologies and formats across a variety of games, recognizing these 'Families' provides an insightful access into the broad, shared infrastructure. This chapter aims to unveil the concept of 'Game Families,' highlighting the commonalities between games from the same lineage. It further explains how such a classification simplifies the file format decoding, given the shared settings and small iterations between games under the same family. The grasp of this classification system will help you appreciate the continuity and progression of game design and technology, thereby serving as a foundational tool on your exploration journey.
